        "Educational Example",
        "Application Demonstration"
      ],
      "skos:definition": "M0 ontologies created primarily for educational, illustrative, or exploratory purposes. Unlike Poclets, Case Studies may be incomplete (missing ASFID types) or over-specified (non-minimal).",
      "rdfs:comment": "Case Studies demonstrate TSCG application without the rigor required of Poclets. They serve pedagogical or experimental roles and may evolve into full Poclets after validation.",
      "m3:semanticSignature": "pedagogical + may_be_incomplete + evolves_toward_Poclet",
